<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 7:57AM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of central Sevier and
northeastern Howard Counties through 815 AM CDT...
At 757 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Umpire to 7 miles west of Dierks to near
Lockesburg. Movement was east at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Dierks, Umpire, Lockesburg, Corinth, Center Point, Athens, Muddy
Fork, Lebanon, Silver Ridge, Burg and Provo.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 PM CDT for southwestern
Arkansas.</instruction>
